Slurm

```json
{
  "application": "Slurm",
  "description": "The script is designed to run on a Slurm cluster. It utilizes Slurm's job submission system to manage resources and execute tasks.",
  "resource_requirements": {
    "memory_per_cpu": "4G",
    "nodes": 1,
    "environment_variables": [
      "PATH",
      "HF_DATASETS_OFFLINE",
      "TRANSFORMERS_OFFLINE",
      "RESULTS_DIR",
      "FEATURE_DATASET_DIR",
      "TRANSFORMERS_CACHE",
      "HF_DATASETS_CACHE",
      "HF_HOME"
    ],
    "python_script": "evaluate_probes.py",
    "python_script_arguments": [
      "--experiment_name $1",
      "--experiment_type $2",
      "--evaluation_type $3",
      "--model $4",
      "--entity_type color",
      "--feature_name red",
      "--feature_name green",
      "--feature_name blue",
      "--feature_name hue",
      "--feature_name saturation",
      "--feature_name value",
      "--feature_name lightness",
      "--feature_name y",
      "--feature_name i",
      "--feature_name q"
    ],
    "conda_environment": "$ORDINAL_PROBING_ROOT/ord/bin/activate"
  },
  "software_requirements": [
    "python",
    "evaluate_probes.py",
    "transformers",
    "datasets",
    "conda"
  ],
  "notes": "The script seems to be designed for evaluating probes for color features, and it leverages the Hugging Face Transformers and Datasets libraries."
}
```
